        <div id="home">
            <div class="big-logo">
                <img src="~/res/landing.jpg" alt="Parsing Illustration">
            </div>
            <div class="motivation">
                <span class="catch-title">Parsing sucks.</span>
                <span class="catch-sub">Predefined algorithm is the answer.</span>
                <span class="catch-text">ctox will help you to parse a program written in C.</span>
                <span class="catch-text">The parser itself is built in C, so it's super fast and reliable.</span>
                <span class="catch-text">Result is written in XML format, so you don't have to worry</span>
                <span class="catch-text">about using parsed program in your context.</span>
                <div class="motivation-buttons">
                    <a href="/Auth/Register">
                        <button class="filled">Try it free</button>
                    </a>
                    <a href="#api">
                        <button>Any more?</button>
                    </a>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
        <div id="about">
            <span class="high-title">How it works</span>
            <span class="about-text">Parsing is the process of analyzing a string of symbols of computer language </span>
            <span class="about-text">conforming to the rules of a formal grammar.</span>
            <span class="about-text">And <span class="mini-logo">CTOX</span> does it in three steps.</span>
            <div class="about-illust">
                <section>
                    <div class="illust-step">1</div>
                    <div class="illust-title">Lexical analysis</div>
                    <div class="illust-info">Splits string into separate words called lexemes and combines them with useful information, producing tokens.</div>
                </section>
                <section>
                    <div class="illust-step">2</div>
                    <div class="illust-title">Syntax analysis</div>
                    <div class="illust-info">Recursively combines tokens into bigger groups, using some set of rules, in parallel builds abstract syntax tree.</div>
                </section>
                <section>
                    <div class="illust-step">3</div>
                    <div class="illust-title">Serialization</div>
                    <div class="illust-info">Converts abstract parsing tree, which is preseneted in memory as call stack, to a readable and easily parseable format XML.</div>
                </section>
            </div>
        </div>
        <div id="api">
            <div class="description">
                <span class="desc-title">No more boring web UI</span>
                <span class="desc-sub">Start using our API</span>
                <span class="desc-text">You can get your <span class="secret">super-secret</span> API key and send requests</span>
                <span class="desc-text">straightforward to our server without ever logging-in into web interface.</span>
                <span class="desc-text">You get more efficiency and less headaches.</span>
                <span class="desc-text"> Available commands can be found in your personal page.</span>
                <div class="desc-code">
                    <pre class="prettyprint">https://ctox.com/api/test</pre>
                </div>
                <div class="desc-code">
                    <pre class="prettyprint lang-xml">&lt;function&gt;
    &lt;prototype&gt; void test ( ) &lt;/prototype&gt;
    &lt;body&gt;
        &lt;expression hascalls = &quot;true&quot;&gt;
            &lt;funccall&gt;
                &lt;name&gt; printf &lt;/name&gt;
                &lt;arguments&gt; 
                    &quot;%s\n&quot; , &quot;Hello from api!&quot; 
                &lt;/arguments&gt;
            &lt;/funccall&gt;
            &lt;text&gt; printf ( &quot;%s\n&quot; , &quot;Hello from api!&quot; ) &lt;/text&gt;
        &lt;/expression&gt;
    &lt;/body&gt;
&lt;/function&gt;</pre>
                </div>
                <div class="desc-buttons">
